column5: Leaving for Nakina early tomorrow morning. Fish get ready.
They are rumored to be in schools preparing for you.
Oh, your buddies say most of them you will be seeing are currently in elementary school.
Hey OnetimeDave,Our group leaves VT at 10pm tomorrow and looking forward to meeting at the dock. Charlie
Do a good check on ice, some lakes were still solid up around Nakina opening day. Bill
We were told no problem with ice in Nakina area. If so we will fly out of Geraldton.

Just talked with Greg at Nakina Air 5 minutes ago. Yes the ice went out on Monday and they're flying. You guys will be fine.Us on the other hand....He says Windsor will be very iffy for us flying in this Sat. All the lakes that far north still have tons of ice.Sigh.
